Strings and Arrays in Programming
Strings and arrays are important in programming because they help us store and work with data. A string is a sequence of characters used to represent text, such as names, sentences, or documents. For example, in Python:
text = "Hello world"
print(text)
This shows how a string can store and display text like in a document.
An array (called a list in Python) is used to store multiple values in one variable. For example:
names = ["Rose", "John", "Amina"]
print(names[0])
This stores several names and allows us to access each one.
Strings and arrays can also be used together. For example, storing sentences in an array:
sentences = ["Line one", "Line two", "Line three"]
for line in sentences:
    print(line)
